        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 7 at 3:23PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ellicott, or 22 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving southeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ellicott, Yoder and Schriever Space Force Base.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
